sec.p:
A competition gel shift assay previously used for c-di-GMP and c-di-AMP riboswitches (36,46) was modified to measure the binding affinities of c-AMP-GMP and c-di-GMP analogs. A total of 20 nM Gs 1761 was folded in the presence of trace radiolabeled c-AMP-GMP and increasing concentrations of cold c-AMP-GMP analog. The binding reactions were incubated until they had reached equilibrium (at least 19 h) and the bound and unbound cyclic dinucleotide was separated on a native PAGE gel at 4°C. Data were analyzed as described above and the Kd of each analog was determined using the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
